{"type":"message","id":"49ff759e","parentId":"53a24a4b","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:02:31.113Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Resolving Merge Conflicts**\n\nI'm currently dealing with merge conflicts in the codebase. Specifically, the removal and modification of `requirements.txt` across commits are causing issues. Additionally, I see that a file `dmarket_api.py` was added remotely but the directory structure has changed locally, leading to further complications.\n\n\n**Deconstructing Git Conflicts**\n\nThe git conflict is becoming clearer. The `requirements.txt` file was deleted in the base branch, while my commit modified it. The added `dmarket_api.py` in my branch also has an add/add conflict. I'm focusing on understanding how `origin/dev` and my changes interact. I've confirmed that the base branch deleted `requirements.txt`. I think I will use the remote version of requirements, but I need to be sure.\n\n\n**Evaluating Rebase Strategies**\n\nI'm now contemplating a more streamlined approach to resolve these conflicts. The complexity of the merge is growing due to the deletion and modification of key files in the remote branch, alongside the addition/addition conflict with `dmarket_api.py`. My current assessment leads me to a reset, followed by reapplying only the test files. This simplifies the process by isolating my test additions and circumventing more complex merge scenarios.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771167751106_366","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cp -r tests tests_backup\ngit rebase --abort\ngit fetch origin\ngit reset --hard origin/dev\ncp -r tests_backup/* tests/\nrm -rf tests_backup\ngit add tests/\ngit commit -m \"feat: Expanded test suite (Unit, Integration, Perf)\"\ngit push origin dev\ngit rev-parse HEAD"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":56108,"output":691,"cacheRead":52944,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTok