{"type":"message","id":"cd58343a","parentId":"37e93fe3","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:03:44.440Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Examining the test script**\n\nI'm now carefully reviewing `tests/unit/test_json.py`. I'm starting by dissecting the structure of this test script, scrutinizing how test cases are organized and implemented. My aim is to understand the scope and the execution flow of the testing. I'm taking detailed notes as I progress.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771167824433_371","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import json\nimport pytest\n\ntry:\n    import orjson\nexcept ImportError:\n    orjson = None\n\nDATA = {\n    \"string\": \"test\",\n    \"int\": 123,\n    \"float\": 1.23,\n    \"bool\": True,\n    \"none\": None,\n    \"list\": [1, 2, 3],\n    \"dict\": {\"nested\": \"value\"}\n}\n\ndef test_json_compat():\n    \"\"\"Test standard JSON library compatibility.\"\"\"\n    dumped = json.dumps(DATA)\n    loaded = json.loads(dumped)\n    assert loaded == DATA\n\n@pytest.mark.skipif(orjson is None, reason=\"orjson not installed\")\ndef test_orjson_compat():\n    \"\"\"Test orjson library compatibility against standard JSON.\"\"\"\n    # orjson dumps to bytes\n    or_dumped = orjson.dumps(DATA)\n    json_dumped = json.dumps(DATA).encode('utf-8')\n\n    # Compare structure after loading back\n    assert orjson.loads(or_dumped) == DATA\n    assert json.loads(or_dumped) == DATA\n\n    # Verify orjson can load std json output\n    assert orjson.loads(json_dumped) == DATA\n","file_path":"tests/unit/test_json.py"},"thoughtSignature":"CiQBjz1rXzc7MKGHwHyPc+hS9wCNCjWHHNiSlqYw/sYg3C4kkOAKOgGPPWtfZ1fi3rsDdyMbIYgEriBPw70n2HArIAzpcOSxHdQAzbqcKYrTl4p7MkO0PsBNVrDb5WOvsLkKIgGPPWtfKPytZPlbIL8FPDX+QfX7rCtA6WY0CjUtFBHMfVc="}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":66965,"output":319,"cacheRead":7634,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67284,"cost":{"input":0.1339