{"type":"message","id":"b8f871d2","parentId":"f98ebe4f","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:03:57.930Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing Performance Tests**\n\nI'm currently focused on the `test_latency.py` file, examining how performance tests are structured. I'm noting the specific metrics being tracked and the methodologies employed to measure latency. My goal is to understand the robustness of the testing framework.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771167837924_373","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"tests/perf/test_latency.py","content":"import asyncio\nimport time\nimport pytest\n\n# Performance constraint: Critical path should be under 50ms\n\nasync def critical_path_operation():\n    \"\"\"Simulate a critical path operation for latency testing.\"\"\"\n    await asyncio.sleep(0.01)  # 10ms\n    return True\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_latency_critical_path():\n    \"\"\"Verify that critical path operations complete within 50ms.\"\"\"\n    start_time = time.perf_counter()\n\n    await critical_path_operation()\n\n    end_time = time.perf_counter()\n    duration_ms = (end_time - start_time) * 1000\n\n    print(f\"\\nLatency: {duration_ms:.2f}ms\")\n\n    # Assert < 50ms\n    assert duration_ms < 50.0, f\"Latency too high: {duration_ms}ms > 50ms\"\n"},"thoughtSignature":"CiQBjz1rX2uAsaUecHhBKunrHFQ7ZoQXZPDG7sTlXCppN8hAHvUKPQGPPWtfceTmHTCNP9x05fHo5Z/01s3k4bKA7pujYCssPiBlKErLohEo5R8Cb+ONlTKtq+QD8XMYDX7O584KIgGPPWtfcwN/vaxLq80DYKbGXu5aYn/BdpAGLUWzAtltX7Y="}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":67919,"output":244,"cacheRead":64991,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68163,"cost":{"input":0.135838,"output":0.002928,"cacheRead":0.012998200000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.15176420000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771167832350}}
{"type":"message","id":"27353a94","parentId":"b8f871d2","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:03:57.946Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"write_1771167837924_373","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 693 bytes to tests/perf/test_latency.py"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771167837944}}
{"type":"message","id":"9015a7af","parentId":"27353a94","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:04:03.618Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Testing the Async Client**\n\nI'm currently focused on the `test_async_client.py` file within the regression tests. My thought process revolves around thoroughly examining the asynchronous client's behavior. I aim to identify potential edge cases and ensure the client functions robustly under various conditions.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771167843614_374","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import asyncio\nimport pytest\n\nclass AsyncClient:\n    \"\"\"A simple async client context manager.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.connected = False\n\n    async def connect(self):\n        \"\"\"Simulate connection.\"\"\"\n        await asyncio.sleep(0.01)\n        self.connected = True\n        return self\n\n    async def close(self):\n        \"\"\"Simulate closing connection.\"\"\"\n        self.connected = False\n\n    async def __aenter__(self):\n        await self.connect()\n        return self\n\n    async def __aexit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb):\n        await self.close()\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_async_client_context_manager():\n    \"\"\"Test that the async context manager connects and disconnects correctly.\"\"\"\n    async with AsyncClient() as client:\n        assert client.connected is True\n        assert isinstance(client, AsyncClient)\n\n    assert client.connected is False\n","file_path":"tests/regression/test_async_client.py"},"thoughtSignature":"CiQBjz1rX1mqCOiwd5D+8MulI66GflaKTuhg9I8T2/aFpOT1pXQKSAGPPWtfi71qL5/37P9BIAAAWprX56z/dEiM69sa/a7cQyf19r49x8QXv9w4wuY487d8kb486EETn5xDhbzKoHpkyg3aIWFLhwoiAY89a19x6hTvfDJwGBE/l8cgMQPTcS6WR6Yzh0nB364m1Q=="}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":68226,"output":253,"cacheRead":65023,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68479,"cost":{"input":0.136452,"o